#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/blood_hawk.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Perception +4    \n"
"**Senses** passive Perception 14    \n"
"**Languages** --    \n"
"**Challenge** 1/8 (25 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/blood_hawk.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Keen Sight.** The hawk has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that "
"rely on sight.    \n"
"**Pack Tactics.** The hawk has advantage on an attack roll against a "
"creature if at least one of the hawk's allies is within 5 feet of the "
"creature and the ally isn't incapacitated. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/blood_hawk.md:26
msgid ""
"### Actions **Beak.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one "
"target. _Hit:_ 4 (1d4 + 2) piercing damage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/blood_hawk.md:28
msgid ""
"### Description Taking its name from its crimson feathers and aggressive "
"nature, the blood hawk fearlessly attacks almost any animal, stabbing it "
"with its daggerlike beak. Blood hawks flock together in large numbers, "
"attacking as a pack to take down prey."
msgstr ""
